<h1>Looper Board Game Rules</h1>

<h2>Overview</h2>
<p>A strategy-based story-driven board game inspired by the movie <em>Looper</em>, where players take on the roles of key characters with conflicting goals. Time travel, moral decisions, and psychic powers shape every turn.</p>

<h2>Characters and Objectives</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Young Joe</strong>: Gain Saraâ€™s trust, protect the Rainmaker, overcome greed, and prevent Rainmaker from turning into a villain.</li>
  <li><strong>Old Joe</strong>: Locate and eliminate Rainmaker candidates, avoid capture, change the future.</li>
  <li><strong>Gat Man</strong>: Capture either Joe, maintain order.</li>
  <li><strong>Sara</strong>: Protect Rainmaker, keep him emotionally stable, survive attacks.</li>
  <li><strong>Rainmaker (NPC)</strong>: Psychic outbursts when destabilized. Pushes characters randomly.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Board Locations</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Farmhouse (Sara's Home)</li>
  <li>City</li>
  <li>Hideout</li>
  <li>Abandoned School</li>
  <li>Train Station</li>
  <li>Three Unknown Houses (Rainmaker candidates)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Card Types</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Action Cards</strong>: Move, Heal, Hide, Investigate, Set Trap, Psychic Pulse</li>
  <li><strong>Event Cards</strong>: Time Glitch, Psychic Surge, Weapon Jammed, Memory Reveal</li>
  <li><strong>Character Objective Cards</strong>: Varies per player (see full rules)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Winning Conditions</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Young Joe: Protects Rainmaker and survives</li>
  <li>Old Joe: Eliminates candidates</li>
  <li>Sara: Survives and keeps Rainmaker calm</li>
  <li>Gat Man: Captures either Joe</li>
</ul>
